 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.7","title":"[FTUI][G7] Integrate unit + snapshot + E2E suites into quality-gate runner with triage output","description":"Unify FTUI verification into a repeatable quality-gate workflow (local + CI) that runs unit tests, snapshot/golden tests, and E2E scripts with detailed logs. Standardize failure taxonomy and artifact locations so contributors can debug regressions quickly without guesswork.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:47:12.794960489Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-08T19:59:32.012086280Z","closed_at":"2026-02-08T19:59:32.012060682Z","close_reason":"Superseded by canonical FTUI plan in coding_agent_session_search-2dccg; keep only canonical graph active to avoid duplicate execution.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ci","ftui","logging","quality-gates","testing","ui"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.7","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:47:12.794960489Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.7","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:54:40.750915703Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":265,"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Execution guidance for G7:\\n- Unify verification into one documented gate workflow that is identical in intent across local/CI.\\n- Include cargo checks/clippy/fmt/test plus FTUI snapshot and E2E suites with clear pass/fail sections.\\n- Standardize artifact locations and failure taxonomy so any contributor can debug without tribal knowledge.\\n- Gate must fail hard on unresolved critical regressions; no soft-pass ambiguity.","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:55:34Z"},{"id":315,"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.7","author":"ubuntu","text":"Reopened: Reopened to keep the FTUI rehabilitation plan active after bulk-close while planning is still in progress.","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:58:09Z"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.8","title":"[FTUI][G8] Document FTUI test-observability playbook (logs, artifacts, rerun workflows)","description":"Write self-contained guidance for reading FTUI regression logs, interpreting artifact bundles, reproducing failures, and distinguishing true regressions from expected visual changes. Include canonical command recipes and evidence requirements for closure/sign-off.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:47:13.383817797Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-08T19:59:32.172915012Z","closed_at":"2026-02-08T19:59:32.172890086Z","close_reason":"Superseded by canonical FTUI plan in coding_agent_session_search-2dccg; keep only canonical graph active to avoid duplicate execution.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["docs","ftui","observability","testing","ui"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.8","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:47:13.383817797Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.8","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:54:41.308744267Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":266,"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.8","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Documentation contract for G8:\\n- Playbook must be self-contained for future contributors with zero historical context.\\n- Include canonical rerun commands, expected outputs, troubleshooting decision tree, and evidence requirements.\\n- Explicitly document how to interpret structured E2E logs and snapshot diff bundles.","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:55:34Z"},{"id":316,"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.8","author":"ubuntu","text":"Reopened: Reopened to keep the FTUI rehabilitation plan active after bulk-close while planning is still in progress.","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:58:09Z"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.9","title":"[FTUI][G9] Remove legacy-default pinning and verify FTUI-first release posture","description":"After all quality gates pass, remove any remaining legacy-default or temporary visual fallback pinning that prevents FTUI from being the clear default. Validate startup/runtime paths and release artifacts to ensure FTUI behavior is the authoritative shipped experience.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:47:13.888802182Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-08T19:59:32.006688263Z","closed_at":"2026-02-08T19:59:32.006666422Z","close_reason":"Superseded by canonical FTUI plan in coding_agent_session_search-2dccg; keep only canonical graph active to avoid duplicate execution.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ftui","quality-gates","release","ui"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.9","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:47:13.888802182Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.9","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:54:43.026891007Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.9","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:54:42.450221392Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":267,"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.9","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Release posture contract for G9:\\n- Do not remove legacy/default pinning until objective gates pass.\\n- After unpinning, validate startup/runtime paths to confirm FTUI-first behavior is authoritative.\\n- Document rollback strategy and known residual risks in release notes/sign-off packet.","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:55:34Z"},{"id":317,"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3ns08.7.9","author":"ubuntu","text":"Reopened: Reopened to keep the FTUI rehabilitation plan active after bulk-close while planning is still in progress.","created_at":"2026-02-08T19:58:09Z"}]}
-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd","title":"EPIC: ftui-ux — Premium TUI Experience via FrankenTUI Feature Suite","description":"Elevate the cass TUI from functional to world-class by fully leveraging the FrankenTUI (ftui) feature suite already compiled into the binary but underutilized. Number one user request: pressing Enter on a search result should open a beautiful full-conversation modal with GitHub-Flavored Markdown rendering. Beyond that the massive analytics data we collect (18+ metrics, 10+ derived metrics, dual-track rollups) should be displayed using ftui rich data viz (BarChart, LineChart, Sparkline, Canvas, visual-fx). ftui-extras provides: markdown (MarkdownRenderer with full GFM), syntax (code block highlighting), charts (BarChart LineChart Sparkline), canvas (Painter API), visual-fx (animations gradients), forms+validation, help, theme, clipboard, export. Already have but need to enhance: Detail modal with 4 tabs and MarkdownRenderer; 8 analytics views; analytics data with rollups; chart rendering. Missing: detail modal GFM needs polish, analytics charts underuse ftui features, search results lack inline analytics, no smooth view transitions. Goals: (1) Premium Enter-to-detail-modal reading experience (2) Surface analytics data using full viz toolkit (3) Bidirectional flow search-to-analytics and analytics-to-search (4) Ship incremental value. Constraints: Rust 2024 nightly, Elm architecture, wildcard deps, 16ms frame budget, tests clean after every change.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:56:37.050974442Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T05:56:37.050974442Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","title":"Feature A: Detail Modal as Premium GFM Reading Experience","description":"The centerpiece deliverable: when a user selects a search result and presses Enter, a modal opens showing the complete conversation rendered in beautiful GitHub-Flavored Markdown. This must rival GitHub issue/PR reading quality. Currently the detail modal exists (DetailTab enum with Messages/Snippets/Raw/Json tabs, MarkdownRenderer integration, role-based gutters) but needs significant enhancement: code blocks lack syntax highlighting, tool calls are not collapsible, no session-level analytics, and the overall reading experience needs polish. The MarkdownRenderer from ftui_extras::markdown already supports headings, code blocks, tables, task lists, admonitions, math, footnotes — we just need to wire everything up properly and add the missing UX pieces. Key files: src/ui/app.rs (detail modal at lines 5740-5841, DetailTab enum at line 817, show_detail_modal state at line 3553), src/ui/style_system.rs (markdown_theme() at lines 1029-1068).","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:56:49.286275778Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T05:56:49.286275778Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:56:49.286275778Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd","title":"EPIC: ftui-ux — Premium TUI Experience via FrankenTUI Feature Suite","description":"Elevate the cass TUI from functional to world-class by fully leveraging the FrankenTUI (ftui) feature suite already compiled into the binary but underutilized. Number one user request: pressing Enter on a search result should open a beautiful full-conversation modal with GitHub-Flavored Markdown rendering. Beyond that the massive analytics data we collect (18+ metrics, 10+ derived metrics, dual-track rollups) should be displayed using ftui rich data viz (BarChart, LineChart, Sparkline, Canvas, visual-fx). ftui-extras provides: markdown (MarkdownRenderer with full GFM), syntax (code block highlighting), charts (BarChart LineChart Sparkline), canvas (Painter API), visual-fx (animations gradients), forms+validation, help, theme, clipboard, export. Already have but need to enhance: Detail modal with 4 tabs and MarkdownRenderer; 8 analytics views; analytics data with rollups; chart rendering. Missing: detail modal GFM needs polish, analytics charts underuse ftui features, search results lack inline analytics, no smooth view transitions. Goals: (1) Premium Enter-to-detail-modal reading experience (2) Surface analytics data using full viz toolkit (3) Bidirectional flow search-to-analytics and analytics-to-search (4) Ship incremental value. Constraints: Rust 2024 nightly, Elm architecture, wildcard deps, 16ms frame budget, tests clean after every change.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:56:37.050974442Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T19:48:37.351725198Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T19:48:37.351701134Z","close_reason":"Completed: Feature A/B/C/D delivered and closed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","title":"Feature A: Detail Modal as Premium GFM Reading Experience","description":"The centerpiece deliverable: when a user selects a search result and presses Enter, a modal opens showing the complete conversation rendered in beautiful GitHub-Flavored Markdown. This must rival GitHub issue/PR reading quality. Currently the detail modal exists (DetailTab enum with Messages/Snippets/Raw/Json tabs, MarkdownRenderer integration, role-based gutters) but needs significant enhancement: code blocks lack syntax highlighting, tool calls are not collapsible, no session-level analytics, and the overall reading experience needs polish. The MarkdownRenderer from ftui_extras::markdown already supports headings, code blocks, tables, task lists, admonitions, math, footnotes — we just need to wire everything up properly and add the missing UX pieces. Key files: src/ui/app.rs (detail modal at lines 5740-5841, DetailTab enum at line 817, show_detail_modal state at line 3553), src/ui/style_system.rs (markdown_theme() at lines 1029-1068).","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:56:49.286275778Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T19:47:35.537373504Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T19:47:35.537344781Z","close_reason":"Completed: all Feature A subtasks closed, including A.6 regression suite","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:56:49.286275778Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.1","title":"A.1: Audit and harden Enter-to-detail-modal flow end-to-end","description":"WHAT: Verify that pressing Enter on a selected search result reliably opens the detail modal with the full conversation loaded. Trace the complete flow: KeyEvent::Enter in key handler → CassMsg::DetailOpened → update() sets show_detail_modal=true and triggers conversation fetch → view() renders modal overlay. Document any edge cases where Enter fails (no selection, empty results, stale cache, network fetch in progress). WHY: This is the single most important UX flow in the app. If Enter does not reliably open the detail modal, nothing else matters. Prior bead dcor9.1 addressed routing precedence bugs — verify those fixes are solid. HOW: (1) Read the Enter key handling in app.rs key dispatch, (2) trace DetailOpened message handling in update(), (3) verify cached_detail loading including cache miss path, (4) add focused unit tests for edge cases (no selection, empty query, rapid Enter presses). KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs — search for DetailOpened, show_detail_modal, cached_detail. ACCEPTANCE: Enter opens modal for any selected result with full conversation within 200ms, with graceful handling of edge cases.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:01.743800622Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T08:53:43.395429084Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T08:53:43.395403105Z","close_reason":"Completed: hardened ToggleJsonView and ViewRaw push_trap guards, added 3 edge-case tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.1","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:01.743800622Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.2","title":"A.2: Enhance detail modal with full GFM rendering and syntax-highlighted code blocks","description":"WHAT: Ensure the detail modal renders all GitHub-Flavored Markdown features at high quality: headings (h1-h6 with proper sizing), fenced code blocks with syntax highlighting (using ftui syntax feature and language detection), inline code with background, tables (aligned columns with borders), task lists (checkboxes), blockquotes (with border gutter), bold/italic/strikethrough, links (underlined with info color), horizontal rules, admonitions (note/tip/important/warning/caution with color-coded boxes), and footnotes. WHY: The whole point of the detail modal is to make reading agent conversations pleasant. LLM output is almost always markdown — good rendering is critical. Currently MarkdownRenderer is used but we need to verify all GFM features render correctly and that syntax highlighting works for code blocks (agents produce lots of code). HOW: (1) Check current MarkdownRenderer integration at app.rs:5741-5828, (2) verify MarkdownTheme mapping in style_system.rs:1029-1068 covers all GFM elements, (3) ensure syntax highlighting feature is wired (ftui_extras syntax feature is enabled in Cargo.toml), (4) test with real agent conversations containing diverse markdown, (5) fix any rendering gaps. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (build_messages_lines, detail rendering), src/ui/style_system.rs (markdown_theme()), Cargo.toml (ftui-extras features). ACCEPTANCE: All GFM elements render correctly, code blocks show syntax-highlighted content with language label, tables are aligned, admonitions are color-coded.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:02.142661540Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T09:19:13.360135915Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T09:19:13.360103645Z","close_reason":"Completed: wired syntax highlighting via with_syntax_theme(), themed table borders/headers, added 2 tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.2","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:02.142661540Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.2","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.099340339Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.3","title":"A.3: Implement collapsible tool call sections in detail modal","description":"WHAT: Tool calls in agent conversations are often very long (file reads, bash output, search results) and dominate the conversation view. Implement collapsible sections: show tool call header (tool name, duration, truncated first line) in a compact bar that can be expanded with Enter/Space to reveal full content. System messages should also be collapsible by default. WHY: A typical Claude Code conversation has 50-80% tool call content by volume. Without collapse, users must scroll through pages of file contents and command outputs to find the actual assistant reasoning. This is the single biggest UX pain point in the detail modal. HOW: (1) Add collapsed_tools: HashSet<usize> state tracking which tool call indices are collapsed, (2) in build_messages_lines(), render collapsed tool calls as single-line summary bars with expand indicator, (3) handle Enter/Space on tool call bars to toggle collapse state, (4) default all tool calls to collapsed, with Ctrl+E to expand all / Ctrl+Shift+E to collapse all. Consider using the existing ftui forms feature for interactive expansion. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (detail modal rendering, message iteration). ACCEPTANCE: Tool calls render as compact one-line summaries by default, expand on interaction, with keyboard shortcuts for bulk expand/collapse.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:02.541858484Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T09:32:45.699006228Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T09:32:45.698978506Z","close_reason":"Implemented collapsible tool call sections in detail modal. Added collapsed_tools HashSet state, ToolCollapseToggled/ToolExpandAll/ToolCollapseAll CassMsg variants with handlers, keyboard shortcuts (e/c) in detail modal intercept, auto-collapse on DetailOpened, and one-line summary bar rendering for collapsed messages with triangle indicators. 4 tests added, all passing, clippy clean.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:02.541858484Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.171680283Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.4","title":"A.4: Add session metadata header with inline analytics to detail modal","description":"WHAT: Add a rich header bar at the top of the detail modal showing: agent name (with icon/color), workspace path, session timestamp and duration, message count breakdown (user/assistant/tool), total API tokens, estimated cost, and a mini sparkline of message activity over the session timeline. WHY: When reading a conversation, the user needs context: which agent, what workspace, how long did it run, how much did it cost. Currently this metadata exists in the search hit but is not prominently displayed in the modal. The analytics data is already computed and stored — we just need to surface it. HOW: (1) When opening detail modal, query analytics for the specific session (conversation_id), (2) render a 2-3 line header block with the metadata, (3) use Sparkline widget for the mini activity timeline, (4) make the header sticky (does not scroll with content). KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (detail modal rendering), src/analytics/query.rs (query functions), src/ui/analytics_charts.rs (sparkline rendering helpers). ACCEPTANCE: Detail modal header shows agent, workspace, timestamp, duration, message counts, token total, cost estimate, and activity sparkline.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:02.952792550Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T09:41:59.697709408Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T09:41:59.697678390Z","close_reason":"Implemented sticky session metadata header in detail modal. Shows agent name (with accent color), workspace, source, timestamps, duration, message count breakdown (user/agent/tool/system), token count, and a Unicode text sparkline of message activity. Header is sticky (rendered above scrollable content) on Messages tab only. Includes build_detail_header_lines() and build_text_sparkline() methods. 4 tests added, clippy clean.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.4","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:02.952792550Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.4","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.242198544Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.5","title":"A.5: Enhanced keyboard navigation in detail modal","description":"WHAT: Add message-level navigation: (1) n/N or j/k to jump between messages (skip tool calls), (2) [ and ] to jump between user messages specifically, (3) g/G for top/bottom, (4) / to activate find-in-conversation (already partially implemented via DetailFindState), (5) Tab to cycle between detail tabs (Messages/Snippets/Raw/Json), (6) o to open source session file in external editor, (7) y to copy current message content to clipboard via OSC52. WHY: Conversations can be very long (hundreds of messages). Message-level jumping lets users quickly find the parts they care about. The find feature exists but message-jumping does not. HOW: (1) Add message_positions: Vec<usize> mapping message indices to line offsets in the rendered content, (2) implement jump-to-next-message by finding next message position after current scroll offset, (3) wire keyboard shortcuts in detail modal key handler. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (detail modal key handling, scroll state). ACCEPTANCE: n/N jumps between messages, brackets jump between user messages, find-in-conversation highlights matches, Tab cycles tabs.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:03.378312362Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T09:55:31.247430228Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T09:55:31.247398729Z","close_reason":"Implemented enhanced keyboard navigation in detail modal. Added: detail_message_offsets tracking (RefCell<Vec<(u16, MessageRole)>>), populated during build_messages_lines(). New shortcuts: {/} jump between messages, [/] jump between user messages only, g/G for top/bottom (vim-style). Added DetailMessageJumped CassMsg variant with forward/user_only params. Handler finds next/prev message offset relative to current scroll. 5 tests added, all passing, clippy clean.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.5","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:03.378312362Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.5","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.314653521Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","title":"A.6: Detail modal regression test suite","description":"WHAT: Comprehensive test coverage for the enhanced detail modal: (1) Enter opens modal with correct conversation data, (2) markdown rendering produces expected output for GFM test cases, (3) tool call collapse/expand state management works correctly, (4) message-level navigation jumps to correct positions, (5) find-in-conversation highlights and navigates correctly, (6) session metadata header displays accurate data, (7) performance: modal open under 200ms, markdown render under 5ms per message. WHY: The detail modal is the most complex interactive component — regressions here are high-impact. The existing tests cover basic modal open/close but not the enhanced features. HOW: Unit tests in app.rs for state management (collapse, navigation, find), snapshot tests for rendering output, performance benchmarks. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (test module). ACCEPTANCE: All new features have test coverage, no existing tests broken, performance budgets met.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:03.794268188Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T10:00:19.506785895Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:03.794268188Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.385788200Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.457582908Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.530674601Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2","title":"Feature B: Analytics Data Visualization with Full ftui Chart Suite","description":"We collect massive analytics data (18+ raw metrics, 10+ derived metrics, dual-track rollups at hourly/daily/weekly/monthly granularity) but the 8 existing analytics views (Dashboard, Explorer, Heatmap, Breakdowns, Tools, Cost, Plans, Coverage) underutilize ftui chart capabilities. The ftui-extras crate provides BarChart, LineChart, Sparkline, Canvas (with Painter API for custom rendering), and visual-fx — many of these are imported but not fully exploited. This feature enhances the analytics views to use the full ftui visualization toolkit: interactive drill-down from charts to filtered search results, canvas-rendered custom visualizations, richer chart interactivity, and hourly granularity surfacing. Key files: src/ui/analytics_charts.rs (2518 lines, renders all 8 views), src/analytics/query.rs (timeseries/breakdown/tool queries), src/analytics/types.rs (UsageBucket with all metrics).","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:08.994704526Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:08.994704526Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:08.994704526Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","title":"A.6: Detail modal regression test suite","description":"WHAT: Comprehensive test coverage for the enhanced detail modal: (1) Enter opens modal with correct conversation data, (2) markdown rendering produces expected output for GFM test cases, (3) tool call collapse/expand state management works correctly, (4) message-level navigation jumps to correct positions, (5) find-in-conversation highlights and navigates correctly, (6) session metadata header displays accurate data, (7) performance: modal open under 200ms, markdown render under 5ms per message. WHY: The detail modal is the most complex interactive component — regressions here are high-impact. The existing tests cover basic modal open/close but not the enhanced features. HOW: Unit tests in app.rs for state management (collapse, navigation, find), snapshot tests for rendering output, performance benchmarks. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (test module). ACCEPTANCE: All new features have test coverage, no existing tests broken, performance budgets met.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:03.794268188Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T19:47:16.629565845Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T19:47:16.629537382Z","close_reason":"Completed: added cache-hit open, markdown GFM, and find-navigation regression coverage; full quality gates passed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:03.794268188Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.385788200Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.4","type":"blocks","