-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3","title":"Feature C: Bidirectional Search-Analytics Integration","description":"Create seamless flow between search results and analytics: (1) when viewing a session in the detail modal, show per-session analytics (token usage, cost, tool calls, message timeline) as a sidebar or tab, (2) when viewing analytics charts, clicking/selecting a data point drills down to filtered search results for that agent/workspace/time period, (3) inline mini-analytics in the search result list items (sparklines, token counts, cost). This bridges the gap between the search and analytics experiences, making the TUI feel like a unified intelligence tool rather than two separate modes. Key files: src/ui/app.rs (analytics view routing at lines 8114-8119, detail modal, search result rendering), src/analytics/query.rs (query builders), src/ui/analytics_charts.rs (chart rendering).","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:09.358336068Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:09.358336068Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:09.358336068Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
