 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.1","title":"C.1: Add per-session analytics panel as detail modal tab","description":"WHAT: Add a new Analytics tab to the detail modal (alongside Messages/Snippets/Raw/Json) that shows analytics specific to the current session: token usage timeline (sparkline across messages), cumulative cost curve, tool call frequency, message length distribution, and model used. If the session spans multiple models (e.g. haiku for subagents, opus for main), show the breakdown. WHY: When investigating a specific session, users need to understand its resource profile without leaving the detail view. Questions like 'why was this session so expensive' or 'when did the agent start using too many tokens' are answered by per-session analytics. This is the search-to-analytics direction of the bidirectional flow. HOW: (1) Add DetailTab::Analytics variant, (2) when opening detail modal, query analytics for conversation_id, (3) use Sparkline for token timeline and BarChart for model breakdown, (4) compute cumulative cost as running sum of per-message estimates, (5) show tool call names with counts. Data source: message_metrics table filtered by conversation_id. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (DetailTab enum, detail modal rendering), src/analytics/query.rs (extend or add per-session query). ACCEPTANCE: Analytics tab renders with token timeline, cost curve, tool breakdown, and model split for any session.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:33.618995973Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T09:49:01.383343922Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T09:49:01.383314096Z","close_reason":"Added Analytics tab (DetailTab::Analytics) to detail modal. Shows: Overview (duration, tokens, cost estimate), Message Breakdown (role-colored bar chart), Activity Timeline (text sparkline), Message Length Distribution (stats), Tool Call analysis (frequency bars), Cumulative Content Curve (area sparkline). Tab bar updated with 5 tabs, tab cycling includes Analytics. 3 tests added + 1 existing test updated. All 55+ detail tests pass, clippy clean.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.1","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.183192888Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.1","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.257000364Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.1","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:33.618995973Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.2","title":"C.2: Wire analytics chart selection to search result filtering","description":"WHAT: This is the implementation wiring for B.2 drill-down — when the user presses Enter on a chart element in analytics views, construct the appropriate search filter and switch to search mode. Specific mappings: (1) Agent bar chart → set agent filter, (2) Workspace bar chart → set workspace filter, (3) Heatmap cell → set date range filter to that day, (4) Line chart data point → set date range to that time bucket, (5) Cost model bar → set agent filter (since models correlate with agents). Show a breadcrumb/chip indicating the active drill-down filter. WHY: This completes the analytics-to-search flow. Without it, analytics insights are observational only — users see patterns but cannot investigate them. HOW: (1) Each analytics view emits a DrillDown(AnalyticsFilter) message on Enter, (2) update() converts AnalyticsFilter to search filters (agent, workspace, time range), (3) switch to search mode with filters applied, (4) render breadcrumb showing drill-down source. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (analytics key handling, filter state, view switching), src/ui/analytics_charts.rs (selection state per view). DEPENDS ON: B.2 (chart selection state). ACCEPTANCE: Drill-down from any chart element produces correctly filtered search results with breadcrumb.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:34.113758846Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T09:23:08.208629687Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T09:23:08.208607145Z","close_reason":"Completed via analytics drilldown wiring in src/ui/app.rs: Enter drilldown now maps analytics selections into search filters for agent/workspace/source/time and seeds query for model-cost selections; status breadcrumb reflects origin facets; added drilldown context + override tests and model query-seeding test; validated with check/clippy/fmt and analytics_drilldown test subset.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.2","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.330503764Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.2","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:34.113758846Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.3","title":"C.3: Add inline mini-analytics to search result list items","description":"WHAT: Enrich each search result item in the results list with compact analytics: (1) small token count badge (e.g. '2.1K tok'), (2) cost badge if above threshold (e.g. '$0.42'), (3) message count ('47 msgs'), (4) tiny agent-colored dot indicator. These render in the right margin of each result item, taking advantage of the space that is often empty in wider terminals. WHY: Users currently see title, timestamp, and agent name in results — but not the quantitative dimension. Adding token/cost indicators helps users quickly identify expensive or large sessions without opening the detail modal. This is especially useful for cost investigation workflows. HOW: (1) When loading search results, join with lightweight analytics summary per conversation (total tokens, cost, message count), (2) render badges in the result item right margin, (3) respect LayoutBreakpoint — only show badges on Medium+ terminals, show just token count on MediumNarrow, nothing on Narrow. Data source: daily_stats or a lightweight per-conversation summary. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (result item rendering), src/analytics/query.rs (per-conversation summary query). ACCEPTANCE: Results show token/cost/message badges on Medium+ terminals, data is accurate, no performance regression in result rendering.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:34.598828601Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.401927862Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.401824489Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:34.598828601Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.4","title":"C.4: Cross-feature integration tests for search-analytics flow","description":"WHAT: Integration tests covering the full bidirectional flow: (1) search → select result → open detail modal → switch to Analytics tab → verify data matches, (2) view analytics chart → select element → drill-down → verify search filters correct, (3) search results show inline analytics badges → verify values match detail modal analytics. WHY: The integration between search and analytics involves multiple state transitions and data queries — integration tests catch issues that unit tests miss (e.g. filter construction producing no results, analytics data not matching between views). HOW: Build on existing cross_workstream_integration.rs pattern (1758 lines, 74 tests). Create test fixtures with known analytics data, then verify roundtrip. KEY FILES: tests/cross_workstream_integration.rs (existing pattern), src/ui/app.rs (test module). ACCEPTANCE: All cross-feature flows have integration test coverage.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:35.102137227Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.617247176Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.4","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:35.102137227Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.4","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.472310070Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.4","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.546499106Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.4","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.617181283Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4","title":"Feature D: Visual Polish and Transitions via ftui visual-fx","description":"Use ftui visual-fx feature to add smooth transitions between views, loading animations for data fetching, and gradient accents. Currently view switches are instant cuts — adding brief crossfade or slide animations makes the TUI feel more responsive and polished. Loading states for analytics data fetching (which hits SQLite) should show progress indication. This is lower priority than Features A-C but contributes to the premium feel. Key files: src/ui/app.rs (view transitions in update()), src/ui/ftui_adapter.rs (ftui imports). Note: all animations must respect the DegradationLevel cascade — skip animations when frame budget is tight.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:09.726237980Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:09.726237980Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:09.726237980Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.1","title":"D.1: Add smooth view transition animations using ftui visual-fx","description":"WHAT: Add brief (100-200ms) crossfade or slide transitions when switching between major views (search ↔ analytics, analytics sub-view changes, modal open/close). Currently all view switches are instant hard cuts. WHY: Instant cuts feel jarring and make it hard to track where you are in the UI. Brief transitions provide continuity cues. ftui already has spring-based animation support (STAGGER_DELAY at 30ms, start_staggered_reveal() function exist in app.rs) — we need to extend this to view transitions. HOW: (1) Use ftui visual-fx animation primitives for opacity/position interpolation, (2) on view switch, set a transition_state with source view snapshot, (3) render interpolated blend for transition duration, (4) respect DegradationLevel — skip animations at EssentialOnly and below. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (view switching in update(), STAGGER_DELAY at line 272, start_staggered_reveal at line 415), src/ui/ftui_adapter.rs. ACCEPTANCE: View transitions feel smooth, duration 100-200ms, disabled under degradation.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:58.596656629Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:58.596656629Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.1","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:58.596656629Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.2","title":"D.2: Add loading/progress indicators for async data operations","description":"WHAT: Show loading indicators when: (1) opening detail modal (conversation fetch), (2) switching analytics views (data query), (3) initial index load. Use a spinner or progress bar from ftui, not a blank screen or frozen frame. WHY: Without loading indicators, the TUI appears frozen during data fetches. Analytics queries can take 50-200ms for large datasets, and conversation fetches even longer for remote sources. Users need feedback that the operation is in progress. HOW: (1) Add loading_state: Option<LoadingContext> to app state, (2) set loading on async operation start, clear on completion, (3) render a small spinner widget in the relevant area during loading, (4) ensure loading state integrates with Elm architecture (set in update, render in view). KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (async operation dispatch, view rendering). ACCEPTANCE: All async operations show loading indicator, indicator clears on completion, no visual artifacts.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:59.043619789Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T17:57:08.301671861Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.2","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:59.043619789Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.3","title":"D.3: Visual polish regression tests","description":"WHAT: Tests for animation and loading state features: (1) transition state correctly set and cleared on view switches, (2) loading indicators appear during async operations, (3) animations respect DegradationLevel cascade, (4) no panics or visual artifacts at any terminal size during transitions. WHY: Animation and loading state bugs are subtle — an animation that does not complete leaves the UI in a broken state. Testing ensures reliability. HOW: Unit tests for state management, rendering tests across degradation levels. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (test module). ACCEPTANCE: All visual polish features have test coverage.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:59.414245021Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.765822636Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:59.414245021Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.690582132Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.765752947Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
